<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5349&amp;p=48374#p48374"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Fx3 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br /><em>Bit 5 - more than 8 objects on a single scanline have been detected in the last frame</em><br /><br />would be changed to:<br /><br /><em>Bit 5 - more than 8 objects have been detected in the current frame</em><br /></div><br />Not really... You can have 64 in the same frame and never trigger that bit... Just don't put 8 or more sharing the same scanlines! =)<br /><br />Sprite rendering is scanline-based, so you can't get rid of the word "scanline". I see nothing wrong with the original description, except that 8 sprites can be enough to set the flag. This flag is too complicated to be explained in a single line of text.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Sun Jun 28, 2009 12:21 pm</p><hr />
