<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5349&amp;p=48365#p48365"><![CDATA[
- True, true. So, this thing:<br /><br /><em>Bit 5 - more than 8 objects on a single scanline have been detected in the last frame</em><br /><br />would be changed to:<br /><br /><em>Bit 5 - more than 8 objects have been detected in the current frame</em><br /><br />- Of course this is triggered in a certain scanline; in other words, AFAIK, there's no "frame scanning" for such overflow. Once it's set in scanline N, it remains set until VBlank ends.<br /><br />EDIT: personally, the word "frame" is deprecated. I would use "time" instead.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=39">Zepper</a> — Sun Jun 28, 2009 8:28 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
